question.value:
Given the following Sass code snippet:

$font-stack: Helvetica, sans-serif;
$primary-color: #333;

body {
  font: 100% $font-stack;
  color: $primary-color;
  nav {
    ul {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      list-style: none;
    }
    li { display: inline-block; }
    a {
      display: block;
      padding: 6px 12px;
      text-decoration: none;
    }
  }
}

What will be the compiled CSS for 'nav li a' selector?

Consider the following LESS code:

@width: 10px;
.class {
  @width: 100px;
  .inner { width: @width; }
}

What will be the width of the '.inner' class?

Considering the following Sass and LESS code snippets, which statement is true about the output? 
Sass: 
@mixin adjust-color($color, $amount) {
  @return lighten($color, $amount);
}
.color-div { color: adjust-color(blue, 20%); }

LESS: 
.adjust-color(@color, @amount) {
  color: lighten(@color, @amount);
}
.color-div { .adjust-color(blue, 20%); }
